  "body": {
    "export_view": {
      "value": "<p>RepairQ allows users to attach, or bundle, items within a ticket, which charges customers a flat fee for a repair service while internally tracking the individual costs of parts, inventory, and labor separately. When an item is bundled under another item on a ticket, the price of the bundled item does not contribute to the overall ticket total. Instead, the cost of the bundled item, referred to as the Child Item, becomes integrated into the existing parent item\u2019s price. For example, bundling a part under a labor item allows you to remove the part from inventory without disclosing its specific cost to the customer.</p><p>Using this feature along with\u00a0<a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1932591125/Catalog+Items+Device+Compatibility\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1932591125\" data-linked-resource-version=\"16\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Catalog Item Device Compatibility</a>\u00a0can customize your repair process and help make tickets move along more efficiently.</p><p><strong>Auto-Bundling</strong>: This allows you to assign specific Parent/Child bundles for your tickets, allowing for faster ticket updates and accuracy. This is especially useful if you offer a repair service that requires specific parts.</p><p><strong>Auto-Adding</strong>: This is similar to the bundling process, using a parent/child relationship, however, the child item is not bundled under the parent item. Since they aren\u2019t bundled, items that are auto-added retain their price on the ticket.</p><h3 id=\"CatalogItems:Auto-BundleandAuto-Add-AdditionalResources\">Additional Resources</h3><ul><li><p><a class=\"external-link\" href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/servicedesk/customer/portal/9/article/2837905412\" rel=\"nofollow\">Bundling Resources</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1932787785/Catalog+Items+Bundle+Setup\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1932787785\" data-linked-resource-version=\"21\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Catalog Items: Bundle Setup</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/2200764440/Bundle+Parts+on+Tickets\" data-linked-resource-id=\"2200764440\" data-linked-resource-version=\"10\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Bundling Items on Tickets</a></p></li><li><p><a class=\"createlink\" href=\"/wiki/pages/createpage.action?spaceKey=SCD&amp;title=Catalog%20Items%3A%20Bundle%20Required&amp;linkCreation=true&amp;fromPageId=2152726556\">Catalog Items: Bundle Required</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1933672484/Tax+Calculations+for+Bundled+Items\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1933672484\" data-linked-resource-version=\"15\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Tax Calculations for Bundled Items</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1932591125/Catalog+Items+Device+Compatibility\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1932591125\" data-linked-resource-version=\"16\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Catalog Items: Device Compatibility</a></p></li></ul><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" width=\"760\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/2152726556/Instructional%20-%200091cd.png?api=v2\"></span><h2 id=\"CatalogItems:Auto-BundleandAuto-Add-Auto-Bundling\">Auto-Bundling</h2><p><strong>Note</strong>: Before setting up Auto-Bundling, make sure you have established a parent/child relationship for your items. For more information on this, see <a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1932787785/Catalog+Items+Bundle+Setup\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1932787785\" data-linked-resource-version=\"21\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Catalog Items: Bundle Setup</a>.</p><p /><p>Navigate to your Catalog, and search for the item you want to set up as the Parent for the bundle. Next to the Catalog item, click the <strong>Options button</strong> to expand additional actions, then click <strong>Compatibility</strong>.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" alt=\"Auto Bundle 1.5.png\" width=\"760\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/2152726556/Auto%20Bundle%201.5.png?api=v2\"></span><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" alt=\"Auto Bundle 1.png\" width=\"760\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/2152726556/Auto%20Bundle%201.png?api=v2\"></span><p>\u00a0</p><p>Use the search box to find the part you want to add as the Child for the bundle. You can do a keyword search or Advanced Search (<strong>+ button</strong>) to find the part(s) to attach. Select the checkbox under <strong>Auto-bundle part</strong>, then close the window.</p><p><strong>Note</strong>: You can attach multiple items to the Parent item.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" alt=\"Auto Bundle 2.png\" width=\"760\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/2152726556/Auto%20Bundle%202.png?api=v2\"></span><p>\u00a0</p><p>When adding the service to a ticket. You will notice that the child item is now automatically bundled to the Service.<br/><strong>Note</strong>: If unnecessary items are added to the bundle, you can remove them by clicking the <strong>X </strong>next to the child Item.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" alt=\"Auto Bundle 3.png\" width=\"760\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/2152726556/Auto%20Bundle%203.png?api=v2\"></span><h2 id=\"CatalogItems:Auto-BundleandAuto-Add-Auto-Adding\">Auto-Adding</h2><p /><p>Navigate to your Catalog, and search for the item you want to set up as the Parent for Auto-add. Next to the Catalog item, click the <strong>Options button</strong> to expand additional actions, then click <strong>Compatibility</strong>.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" alt=\"Auto Bundle 1.5.png\" width=\"760\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/2152726556/Auto%20Bundle%201.5.png?api=v2\"></span><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" alt=\"Auto Bundle 1.png\" width=\"760\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/2152726556/Auto%20Bundle%201.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p>Use the search box to find the part you want to auto-add to the Parent item. Select the checkbox under <strong>Auto-add</strong>, then close the window. When adding the Parent Item to a ticket, the child item is now automatically added to the ticket, but it is not bundled.</p><p><strong>Note</strong>: You can attach multiple items to the Parent item. </p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" alt=\"Auto Bundle 6.png\" width=\"760\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/2152726556/Auto%20Bundle%206.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p /><p>START 1.21.X</p>",
